The paper deals with the vulnerability of autonomous driving systems to adversarial attacks, specifically using LiDAR-based detection systems. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques for object detection and recognition, as well as robotics (RO) for autonomous driving. The paper also discusses the use of optimization algorithms and machine learning (ML) techniques for generating adversarial objects, which falls under artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (LG). Finally, the paper also touches upon the security aspects of autonomous driving systems, which could fall under computer security and cryptography (CR).
